We applied statistical measures of association (Pearson’s correlation [rP] and mutual information [MI]) together [42] to identify miRs and mRNAs which showed a strong inverse association across the LM-MEL dataset. Mutual information is an information-theoretic metric that measures divergence from statistical independence [43]. It contains a \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
